# Acorn Development Guide

## Must Know

### After Modifying Code - MUST RUN
```bash
mvn clean install  # Required! avia-base depends on this library
```

## Key Concepts

### Data Model: Archetype-Driven Attribute Inheritance
- First-level folders (e.g., `/A320`, `/A330`) have `archetype: "csdb"`
- Sub-folders inherit attributes from parent (pre-computed at creation)
- Attributes stored **directly on folder nodes** (not in `attributeMap` child node)

### JCR Session Pattern
```java
Session session = null;
try {
    session = repository.login(new SimpleCredentials("admin", "admin".toCharArray()));
    // ... operations ...
    session.save();
} catch (RepositoryException e) {
    throw new RuntimeException("User-friendly message", e);
} finally {
    if (session != null) session.logout();
}
```

### Use PropertyUtil for JCR Properties
- `PropertyUtil.getSingleValue()` / `setProperty()` for single-value
- `PropertyUtil.getValues()` for multi-value

## Validation Rules
- Folder names: **no spaces** (enforced at service layer)
- Delete with children: requires `force=true`

## Implementation Status
- ✅ Folder CRUD with direct attribute storage
- ✅ Pre-computed attribute inheritance
- 🔄 Unified attribute storage model
- 📅 Tree API migration
- 📅 File service with version control

## Key References
- System Architecture: `../docs/arch/New-Architecture.md`
- Testing: `../avia-base/AGENTS.md`

